==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dovers Powder
<hw>Do"ver's Pow"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From Dr. <ets>Dover</ets>,
an English physician.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A powder of ipecac
and opium, compounded, in the United States, with sugar of milk, but in
England (as formerly in the United States) with sulphate of potash, and
in France (as in Dr. Dover's original prescription) with nitrate and
sulphate of potash and licorice. It is an anodyne diaphoretic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dove's-foot</ent>⟦br⟧
